<![endif]--><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand. Since August 20=
18, Tesla has done four stock offerings raising a total of more than $13 bi=
llion, which it has used to, you know, make cars and become huge. Would it =
have been able to go back to its private backers for $13 billion of capital=
 after doing the largest leveraged buyout in history? Maybe, I don=E2=80=99=
t know; private markets were pretty generous for much of that time. But the=
 public market=C2=A0was=C2=A0<em>extremely=C2=A0</em>generous to Tesla. The=
 last two of those offerings, for $5 billion each, were <a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25472439.275794/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb=
