ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> at-the-market offerings</a> to M=
usk=E2=80=99s horde of retail-investor fans; one of them was timed to Tesla=
=E2=80=99s addition to the S&amp;P 500 index. You can=E2=80=99t do a retail=
 at-the-market offering, or an index-add offering,=C2=A0with a private comp=
any. Tesla's cost of capital is incredibly, incredibly low, because it rais=
es money not from a handful of professional private equity investors but fr=
om an army of Tesla enthusiasts. It is good to have a low cost of capital i=
f you are in a capital-intensive business.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
Even more important, look, Elon Musk runs a trillion-dollar company. If he =
had taken it private, he would be running a company that he bought for $80-=
odd=C2=A0billion in 2018 and that had improved its financial performance si=
nce then. How much would it be worth? Who knows? It wouldn=E2=80=99t trade =
publicly. Retail investors couldn=E2=80=99t bid up the price. It would be w=
orth some vague amount north of $80 billion. =E2=80=9CIf Musk were to take =
Tesla public again,=E2=80=9D analysts might write, =E2=80=9Che might be abl=
e to get as much as a $400 billion valuation,=E2=80=9D or whatever. Might s=
omeone have written =E2=80=9Che might be able to get $1 trillion=E2=80=9D? =
Sure, why not. But that wouldn=E2=80=99t be an <em>accepted fact</em>. The =
value of Tesla would be some unknown number because it wouldn=E2=80=99t tra=
de. Who would believe it was $1 trillion?</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">T=
oday Bloomberg=E2=80=99s billionaire list tells me that Musk is the richest=
 person in the world, with a net worth of $288.6 billion, consisting mostly=
 of Tesla stock. Jeff Bezos is in second place with $192.6 billion of mostl=
y Amazon.com Inc. stock. Musk was well behind Bezos last year, but he=E2=80=
=99s up $118.9 billion year-to-date, because Tesla=E2=80=99s stock has been=
 on a tear. No public stock, no tear, no =E2=80=9Crichest person on Earth.=
=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s nice to be the richest person on earth! I assume.</p=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course in some sense he=E2=80=99d be=C2=A0=
<em>economically=C2=A0</em><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
