<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Good advice</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/25472439.275794/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMjYvY2hpbmEtdXJnZXMtZXZlcmdyYW5kZS1mb3VuZGVyLX=
RvLXBheS1kZWJ0LXdpdGgtcGVyc29uYWwtd2VhbHRoP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMjYyMV9NT05FWVNUV=
UZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIxMTAy=
NiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf9da3b29" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;"> is great</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Chinese autho=
rities told billionaire Hui Ka Yan to use his personal wealth to alleviate =
China Evergrande Group=E2=80=99s deepening debt crisis, according to people=
 familiar with the matter.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Beijing=E2=80=99=
s directive to the Evergrande founder came after his company missed an init=
ial Sept. 23 deadline for a coupon payment on a dollar bond, said the peopl=
e, asking not to be identified discussing a private matter. Local governmen=
ts across China are monitoring Evergrande=E2=80=99s bank accounts to ensure=
 company cash is used to complete unfinished housing projects and not diver=
ted to pay creditors, the people said.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=
=E2=80=99s unclear whether Hui=E2=80=99s fortune is big and liquid enough t=
o make a sizable dent in Evergrande=E2=80=99s liabilities, which swelled to=
 more than $300 billion as of June. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">Hui=E2=80=99s net worth has dwindled to about $7.8 billion from $42 bill=
ion at its peak in 2017, according to Bloomberg Billionaires Index estimate=
s. But the figure comes with considerable uncertainty.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">Much of Hui=E2=80=99s known wealth is derived from his co=
ntrolling stake in Evergrande and the cash dividends he=E2=80=99s received =
from the company since its 2009 listing in Hong Kong. Hui has pocketed abou=
t $8 billion over the past decade thanks to Evergrande=E2=80=99s generous p=
ayouts, according to Bloomberg calculations. It=E2=80=99s not known how Hui=
 reinvested those dividends.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I=
 do think that the concept of limited corporate liability is a bit porous=
=C2=A0if you=E2=80=99re a Chinese billionaire. In America, if=C2=A0you=C2=
=A0run a company with $300 billion in debt, and it can=E2=80=99t pay that d=
ebt, and you have $8 billion sitting in your personal bank account,=C2=A0yo=
u say =E2=80=9Cah I wish I could do something for all of my company=E2=80=
=99s creditors but unfortunately my deep commitment to our capitalist econo=
mic system prevents me from paying debts that aren=E2=80=99t mine, my hands=
 are really tied here.=E2=80=9D That is so deeply the American way that Don=
ald Trump <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25472439=
.275794/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAxNi8wNi8xMi9ueXJlZ2lvbi9kb25hbGQ=
tdHJ1bXAtYXRsYW50aWMtY2l0eS5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB478ebbfd" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">did it repeatedly</a> and was elected president for his troubles.</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In China, if you run a company with $300 billion o=
f debt, and it can=E2=80=99t pay that debt, and you have $8 billion sitting=
 in your personal bank account, and the government calls you up to say =E2=
=80=9Chey spend down your bank account to pay that debt,=E2=80=9D the=C2=A0=
<em>only possible answer=C2=A0</em>is =E2=80=9Cyes, that=E2=80=99s what I w=
as already doing, of course, I would never take $8 billion and run and leav=
e my creditors holding the bag.=E2=80=9D Whether or not you signed a person=
al guarantee, you signed a personal guarantee.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">Temperamentally I tend to be a big fan of limited liability, but I do t=
hink that there is something to be said for each system.</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know how much Hui ransacking his couch cushio=
ns for spare change will actually help with Evergrande=E2=80=99s $300 billi=
on of debt, but=C2=A0I suppose if he has cashed out $8 billion then he prob=
ably has enough money to pay off a $100 million interest payment here, a $2=
00 million maturity there. If this is more =E2=80=9Cbridging a temporary li=
quidity problem=E2=80=9D than it is =E2=80=9Cthrowing money into the ocean =
of a catastrophic default,=E2=80=9D maybe his personal fortune will help. B=
ut even if it doesn=E2=80=99t help and Evergrande does default, it is proba=
bly wise for him, personally and politically, not to end up with too much m=
oney.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D=
"0" cellpadding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Libor Robot</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At some level of generality, every big=
 bank has roughly one zillion contracts that all say =E2=80=9Cthe Interest =
Rate=C2=A0for any period shall be Libor plus the Spread,=E2=80=9D or someth=
ing that means the same thing. And due to the demise of Libor (the London i=
nterbank offered rate) and its replacement by SOFR (the Secured Overnight F=
